There is no information available for this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="44C472C38641C3532DD4A3BF1670F89E" pageId="11" pageNumber="468" type="breeding">
<paragraph id="0C6121488641C3532DD4A3BF1670F89E" blockId="11.[1447,2654,1159,2255]" pageId="11" pageNumber="468">
<emphasis id="3EAAFD5A8641C3532DD4A3BF1671F8EE" bold="true" box="[1449,1583,1787,1820]" pageId="11" pageNumber="468">Breeding.</emphasis>
There is no specific information available for this species, but all titis form monogamous breeding pairs. The male provides parental care by carrying the single offspring.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
